  "prompt": "Game of Thrones Season 5 Episode 5 (Kill the Boy): Did Jorah touch Tyrion?",
  "response": "In \"Game of Thrones\" Season 5 Episode 5, titled \"Kill the Boy,\" Jorah Mormont and Tyrion Lannister are traveling together after Jorah has captured Tyrion and is taking him to Daenerys Targaryen. During their journey, they traverse through ruins and eventually sail through the area known as Old Valyria, where they are attacked by stone men (people suffering from advanced Greyscale).\n\nDuring this encounter, Jorah fights off the stone men to protect himself and Tyrion. In the chaos, Tyrion falls into the water and Jorah dives in to save him. After pulling Tyrion out of the water, Jorah physically touches Tyrion to ensure he is safe and to bring him back to the boat.\n\nIt is revealed later in the episode that while Jorah came into contact with the stone men, he was secretly infected with Greyscale. However, there is no indication that Tyrion contracted the disease from their interaction.",
